messages.title: Securing the economy
messages.content: When Lib Dems entered the coalition in 2010, the economy was on the brink. We have taken the tough decisions to clean up Labour's mess, and thanks to these choices, we are now beginning to see the economy recover and growing confidence.

keyPolicies.policyDescription: Borrowing less than Labour, cutting less than the Conservatives.

mentions.tacticalSituation: It's between the Lib Dems and the Conservatives here. Labour can't win in Woking.

issues.economy: Borrowing less than Labour, cutting less than the Conservatives.
